{
  "texts": [
    "In the early stage, most researchers used traditional deep learning methods, such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs), to produce radiology reports.",
    "IU X-RAY proposed by Demner-Fushman et al [1] was a significant step in this direction.",
    "In addition, Shin et al [2] innovatively applied a CNN-RNN model for structured report creation.",
    "Wang et al [3] used a nonhierarchical CNN-long-short term memory approach, emphasizing both semantic and visual cues.",
    "Vinyals et al [4] introduced visual attention mechanisms in the realm of image captioning with CNN-RNN structures."
  ]
}